Auto darkening helmet are really the way to go. It keeps you from snapping
your head every time you want to start to weld. If you know of a local body
guy, ask him if you can have a fender or hood to practice on. My problem has
been grinding off too much weld and having to reweld  the thing again. 

Bob
Owned by a '78 Champagne Edition Westy and a '73 SB Sunny

